of plate helms into bars and then into plat.  <br>
<br>
I know that we have the t-hunt nights every so often to bolster the treasury.  We do this to gain plat for various uses.  What are these:<br>
1.  Tradeskill Development<br>
2.  Buying Siege Parts<br>
3.  Buying wood (to repair doors or build siege)<br>
4.  Buy Guild House (?? - upgrading, etc.)<br>
5.  Others??<br>
<br>
With SD getting more and more involved in rvr, we are going to have increasing costs around siege equipment, repairing doors, etc.  Plus we don't know what the expansion or future patches might have that will require plat to buy  (I'm just guessing on guild housing).<br>
<br>
To prepare for the known and the unknown, my idea is to implement at least one (but possibly 2-3) &quot;Goldrush&quot; teams.  The objective of these teams would be to supply the guild with a steady stream of income.  Although the treasurer would ultimately decide where to best allocate the funds, my thought is that a % would go to tradeskills, a % to RvR, and the remaining % to a general guild fund.<br>
<br>
Let's take DF as an example.  A Goldrush team goes in for 3 hours and each make 100 gold plus 60 diamond seals.  So that's 300 gold for the guild plus three plate helms that can be salvage and then the bars sold or trinketed.  If the bars are sold at vendor prices then that's an addtional 900 gold or so.  Total of about 1.2 plat for an outing.  This is assuming we can get into DF and assuming that we can continue to salvage the plate helms for 133 bars apiece.<br>
<br>
You then multiply this by 2-3 teams.  Each team takes a week and decides to meet once or twice that week (each team makes it's own call) to hunt.  AFter that week they are off for the next 2 weeks as the other 2 teams take over.  So you rotate it around.<br>
<br>
At any point you could freeze the Goldrush program if you feel the guild has adequate funds and that people are getting burnt out on it.  Then reinstate it later on.<br>
<br>
Just an idea.  Thoughts?<br>
<br>
