<br>
Here were the original parameters for bootcamp:<br>
Duration of Boot Camp: 05/19/02 - 06/30/02<br>
Date-Time: Every Sunday @ 3pm EST.<br>
Date-Time: Every Tuesday @ 8pm EST.<br>
Duration: 3-4 hours each outing.<br>
Meeting Location: Prywen Keep bridge<br>
Hunting Location: TBD each day.<br>
<br>
Lvis had set boot camp to run for 6 weeks, basically until July 1.  I think it's good to have a time limit so that people push a little more and you've got definite goals to shoot for.  Plus, at the end of bootcamp the formal commitment is done if you will.<br>
<br>
The days/times can obviously be whatever works best for most members.  The Sunday time works well for me personally, though the Tuesday time down not (typically).<br>
<br>
I found that you want about 3 hours mimimum, and I've been in boot camps that lasted more like 5 hours.  So there is flexibility there.<br>
<br>
Typically we went to DF whenever possible.  That used to be easier than it seems today, so DM might be a good backup?<br>
<br>
Finally we'd need someone to lead it, someone who has a stake in actually leveling their character (imo).<br>
<br>
